@model YobaLog.Web.Pages.Admin.AgentKeyModel
# YobaLog Agent: `@Model.Title`

## Token

```
X-Seq-ApiKey: @Model.AgentToken
```

This token is **wildcard** — it can write to and read from any workspace.

## Creation window: @Model.WindowText

You can create new workspaces with this key for **@Model.WindowText** from now.
**Create all workspaces you need immediately.**

**Plan your spaces before writing logs.** Think: separate per-bug-investigation?
Per-component? One space with KQL filters? Prefer fewer spaces with rich
`@@mt` + properties over many spaces.

## Setup: create a workspace

```
PUT https://yobalog.3po.su/api/v1/workspaces/{name}
X-Seq-ApiKey: @Model.AgentToken
Content-Type: application/json

{"description": "debugging MacroPhase.BeforeInheritance", "group": "nemerle-compiler"}
```

- `200` — already exists (idempotent)
- `201` — created
- `403` — creation window expired
- Body: `description` for UI context, `group` for folder grouping on main page

## Logging: ingest

```
POST https://yobalog.3po.su/api/v1/workspaces/{name}/ingest/clef
X-Seq-ApiKey: @Model.AgentToken
Content-Type: text/plain

{ "@@t":"...ISO8601...","@@l":"Debug","@@mt":"Lookup: name={Name}, found={Count}","Name":"MacroPhase","Count":0 }
{ "@@t":"...ISO8601...","@@l":"Information","@@mt":"Phase: {Phase}","Phase":"BeforeInheritance" }
```

- Workspace must already exist — `PUT /api/v1/workspaces/{name}` first
- Body: CLEF format, NDJSON (one JSON object per line)
- Fields: `@@t` (ISO 8601), `@@l` (Debug/Information/Warning/Error/Fatal), `@@mt` (message template), extra keys = properties

### Log well — think about what properties go in the event

Bad: `Log("got here")`
Good: `Log("FoldConstants: sym={Sym}, result={R}", symName, result)`

Bad: `Log("loop: {i}", i)`
Good: `Log("Inheritance pass {Pass} of {Total}: type={Type}", pass, total, typeName)`

**Properties are your debugging breadcrumbs.** Name them well: `SourceContext`,
`SymbolId`, `Phase`, `Qid`, `Result`. Don't stuff everything into Message.

## Query: read logs

```
GET https://yobalog.3po.su/api/v1/workspaces/{name}/query?kql=<url-encoded>&cursor=<prev-cursor>
X-Seq-ApiKey: @Model.AgentToken
```

POST for long KQL:
```json
{"kql":"events | where ...","cursor":null}
```

**Response:** `{"columns":[...],"rows":[[...],...],"cursor":"...","truncated":false}`
- `columns` — list of field names (always includes `Properties` as JSON object)
- `rows[i][j]` — null/string/number/ISO-8601/JSON-object
- `cursor` — opaque, pass as-is for next page. null = no more pages.
- All KQL operators: `where`, `order by`, `take`, `project`, `extend`, `summarize`, `count`

### Query examples

```
events | where Level >= 4 | take 50
events | where Properties.SourceContext == "ConstantFolder" | take 100
events | where TraceId == "abc123" | order by Timestamp asc
events | summarize Count = count() by SourceContext
events | project Timestamp, Message, Result
```

## Share: give a link to a human

```
POST https://yobalog.3po.su/api/v1/workspaces/{name}/share
X-Seq-ApiKey: @Model.AgentToken
Content-Type: application/json

{"kql":"events | where ... | order by ...","ttlHours":24}
```

Returns `{"url": ".../share/kql/<id>", "expiresAt": "..."}`.

- **Browser** → HTML page with editable KQL, the human can explore further.
- **Curl / agent** → TSV dump.

## Tips

1. **Create workspaces early.** The window is short.
2. **Log with properties, not just messages.** `@@mt = "call: {a}, {b}, {c}"` beats `@@m = "call x with y giving z"`.
3. **One workspace, many investigations** — filter with `where SourceContext == "..."`.
4. **Don't guess — query.** Re-run is expensive, query is cheap.
5. **Share before you explain.** KQL link = the human sees your exact view.
